        <h2 class="h-md">Email marketing for local businesses, <span class="accent">answered.</span></h2>
        <p>Common questions from local business owners shopping email tools. More? Email <a href="mailto:founder@thestacc.com">founder@thestacc.com</a>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See more: <a href="/reviews/" class="accent">read tool reviews</a>, <a href="/best/" class="accent">more best-of lists</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">view theStacc pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best free email marketing tool for a local business?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Brevo offers the most generous option: unlimited contacts with 9,000 monthly emails. MailerLite follows with 500 contacts and 12,000 monthly emails. Both include automation on free tiers. Kit allows 10,000 free subscribers but excludes automations.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does email marketing cost for a small business?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Entry-level paid plans range $9-15/month for 500-1,000 contacts. Free plans work for businesses under 500 subscribers. At 5,000 contacts, expect $30-60/month. At 10,000 contacts, plan for $50-100/month depending on platform.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is Mailchimp still the best email marketing tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Mailchimp is most recognized but no longer best-value for local businesses. The free tier dropped to 250 contacts and 500 emails in 2024. Brevo and MailerLite both provide superior free plans. Mailchimp's strength remains universal integration compatibility.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What email marketing tool is best for ecommerce?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Klaviyo excels for ecommerce with deep Shopify/WooCommerce integration and purchase-behavior automation. Omnisend offers comparable functionality at lower cost. Both combine SMS and email with pre-built ecommerce workflows.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Should a local business use email marketing?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. 64% of small businesses use email marketing, returning $36-42 for every $1 spent. Email reaches 90%+ of inboxes versus 5-9% organic social reach. For local businesses without marketing teams, email ranks highest-ROI after Google Business Profile optimization.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How often should a local business send emails?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Weekly is standard. A weekly email with one useful tip plus one promotional element maintains engagement without subscriber fatigue. Start with biweekly if you're building the habit — consistency matters more than frequency early on.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">When should I upgrade from a free email plan to paid?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Upgrade when your list hits the free plan's contact limit, when you need multi-step automation, or when you want to send to your full list in a single blast rather than a daily drip. Once you're within 20% of the free cap, start the upgrade conversation.</div>
        </div>
